  ***Identity Operator***

-Identity operators- *are used to compare the objects, not if they are equal, but if they are actually the same object, with the same memory location:
                     * used for Identity testing.

!   Operator	Description	                                  Example	
    is          Returns True if both variables                x is y
                are the same object
    is not      Returns True if both variables                x is not y
                are not the same object            

    //Example
    >>> a = 34566666                   | >>> f = 3456666
    >>> b = a                          | >>> h = 3456666
    >>> a is b                         | >>> f is h
    ... True                           | ... False
    => id of a and b is same,          | => id of f and h is different,
       and return True                 |    and return False

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

  ***Membership Operator***

-Membership Operator- *are used to test if a sequence is presented in an object.

!    Operator	  Description	                                Example	
    in 	          Returns True if a sequence with the           x in y
                  specified value is present in the 
                  object.		
    not in	      Returns True if a sequence with the           x not in y
                  specified value is not present in the 
                  object.

    //Example
    >>> 3 in [3, 7, 8,9]              |>>> 6 in [3, 7, 8, 9]
    ... True                          |... False
    =>3 is in the list,               |=> 6 is not in the list,
      so, it will return True.        |   and it will return False.  

